# Accessibility Guidelines

## Required Accessibility Features

Implement accessibility features on all interactive elements:

- Add `tabindex="0"` for keyboard navigation
- Include `aria-label` attributes for screen readers
- Implement `onClick` and `onKeyDown` handlers for keyboard interaction
- Add appropriate ARIA attributes for complex components
- Ensure proper semantic HTML structure

## Interactive Elements

For clickable elements that are not buttons or links:
```typescript
<div
  tabIndex={0}
  role="button"
  aria-label="Descriptive label"
  onClick={handleClick}
  onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}
  className="cursor-pointer"
>
  Content
</div>
```

## Keyboard Navigation

- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Implement proper focus management
- Provide visual focus indicators
- Handle Enter and Space key interactions appropriately

## Screen Reader Support

- Use semantic HTML elements when possible
- Provide alternative text for images
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3, etc.)
- Include skip navigation links where appropriate